---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Service — SolarROI"
  description="The rules for using the SolarROI iOS app and SolarROI Pro subscription."
>
  <header class="border-b border-solar-hairline">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 h-16 flex items-center justify-between">
      <a href="/" class="flex items-center gap-2 font-bold tracking-tight">
        <span
          class="inline-block w-3 h-3 rounded-sm bg-solar-orange"
          aria-hidden="true"></span>
        SolarROI
      </a>
      <nav class="flex items-center gap-6 text-sm text-solar-muted">
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-solar-ink">Home</a>
        <a href="/privacy" class="hover:text-solar-ink">Privacy</a>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <p
      class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.18em] uppercase text-solar-orange mb-3"
    >
      Terms of Service
    </p>
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight">
      The basics, in plain English.
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-3 text-solar-muted">
      Last updated: May 5, 2026
    </p>

    <div class="prose mt-12 text-solar-ink leading-relaxed space-y-6 text-[17px]">
      <p>
        These terms govern your use of the SolarROI iOS app ("the app") and
        the SolarROI Pro subscription. By installing or using the app, you
        agree to them. If you don't agree, please uninstall the app.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10">Who can use SolarROI</h2>
      <p>
        SolarROI is built for solar contractors and sales professionals. You
        must be at least 18 years old and able to enter into a binding
        contract to use it. The app is not directed at children.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10">License</h2>
      <p>
        We grant you a personal, non-transferable, non-exclusive license to
        install and use the app on devices you own or control, subject to
        these terms and the Apple Media Services Terms (the standard "EULA"
        you accept when you install any App Store app). You may not copy,
        modify, decompile, reverse-engineer, or redistribute the app or its
        components.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10">SolarROI Pro subscription</h2>
      <p>
        SolarROI is free to use with a small project limit. SolarROI Pro is
        an auto-renewing subscription that unlocks unlimited projects,
        watermark-free PDFs, and custom watermarks.
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
        <li>
          <strong>Price and period.</strong> SolarROI Pro is currently
          $4.99 USD per month. Pricing in other regions is shown by Apple
          at the time of purchase and may vary.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Billing.</strong> Payment is charged to your Apple ID at
          confirmation of purchase. Apple processes the entire transaction;
          we never see your payment details.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Auto-renewal.</strong> The subscription renews
          automatically for the same period at the same price unless you
          cancel at least 24 hours before the end of the current period.
          Apple charges your Apple ID for the renewal.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Managing or cancelling.</strong> You can manage or cancel
          your subscription anytime in <em>Settings → [your Apple ID]
          → Subscriptions</em>. Cancelling stops future renewals; the
          current period continues until it expires.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Refunds.</strong> Refunds are handled by Apple under
          their refund policy. We can't issue refunds directly. To request
          one, visit
          <a
            class="text-solar-orange underline"
            href="https://reportaproblem.apple.com"
            >reportaproblem.apple.com</a
          >.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Price changes.</strong> If we change the subscription
          price, Apple will notify you and ask you to consent before the
          new price takes effect.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10">Estimates, not advice</h2>
      <p>
        SolarROI produces <strong>estimates</strong>. The financial,
        production, and savings figures the app calculates are modeled
        projections — they are not a guarantee of actual system
        performance, savings, payback, tax outcome, or system cost. Many
        real-world factors (weather, shading, roof condition, utility rate
        changes, installation specifics, tax situation) affect actual
        results. SolarROI is not a substitute for professional engineering,
        financial, tax, or legal advice. Before relying on a SolarROI
        proposal for a customer commitment, verify the inputs and consult
        the appropriate qualified professional.
      </p>
      <p>
        You are responsible for the accuracy of the data you enter and for
        anything you communicate to your customers based on the app's
        output.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10">Acceptable use</h2>
      <p>You agree not to:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
        <li>
          Use the app for any unlawful purpose, or to deceive or defraud
          your customers.
        </li>
        <li>
          Misrepresent the app's output as a binding offer, contract,
          guarantee, or as the work of a licensed engineer or financial
          advisor when it isn't.
        </li>
        <li>
          Attempt to interfere with the app, the NREL PVWatts service, or
          Apple's services through automated abuse, scraping at scale, or
          circumvention of subscription gating.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10">Third-party services</h2>
      <p>
        The app integrates with two services described in our
        <a class="text-solar-orange underline" href="/privacy">privacy policy</a>:
        Apple (for geocoding addresses and processing the subscription)
        and the National Renewable Energy Laboratory's PVWatts v8 API
        (for production estimates). Your use of those features is also
        subject to the providers' own terms. We are not responsible for
        outages, errors, or changes in those upstream services.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10">Intellectual property</h2>
      <p>
        The SolarROI app, its name, logo, design, and source code are
        owned by us and protected by copyright and trademark law. Your
        contractor profile, customer projects, and any content you create
        with the app remain yours.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10">Disclaimers and liability</h2>
      <p>
        The app is provided "as is" and "as available," without warranties
        of any kind, express or implied, including merchantability,
        fitness for a particular purpose, or non-infringement. To the
        fullest extent permitted by law, we are not liable for indirect,
        incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages, or for
        lost profits, lost revenue, or lost business arising out of or
        related to your use of the app — including any reliance on the
        app's estimates.
      </p>
      <p>
        Some jurisdictions don't allow certain warranty or liability
        limitations, so some of the above may not apply to you. In that
        case, our liability is limited to the maximum extent permitted by
        applicable law.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10">Termination</h2>
      <p>
        You may stop using the app and cancel SolarROI Pro at any time. We
        may suspend or terminate access if you violate these terms. On
        termination, the license above ends and you must stop using the
        app, but the disclaimers and liability sections survive.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10">Changes to these terms</h2>
      <p>
        If we materially change these terms, we'll update this page and
        bump the date at the top. Continued use of the app after a change
        means you accept the updated terms.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10">Relationship to Apple's terms</h2>
      <p>
        SolarROI is distributed exclusively through Apple's App Store. Your
        use of the app is also governed by Apple's
        <a
          class="text-solar-orange underline"
          href="https://www.apple.com/legal/internet-services/itunes/dev/stdeula/"
          >Licensed Application End User License Agreement</a
        >
        ("Apple's standard EULA") and Apple's
        <a
          class="text-solar-orange underline"
          href="https://www.apple.com/legal/internet-services/itunes/"
          >Media Services Terms</a
        >. Where these terms are silent, Apple's standard EULA applies.
        Where these terms conflict with Apple's standard EULA on a topic
        Apple addresses (such as the scope of license or the manner in
        which the app is distributed), Apple's terms control as required
        by Apple's developer agreement.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10">Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about these terms? Email
        <a class="text-solar-orange underline" href="mailto:support@solarroi.app"
          >support@solarroi.app</a
        >.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
